            ['Short Ratio',    shortRatio!=null?fmt(shortRatio,2)+' days':'N/A', 'days to cover'],
          ])}
          ${currentRatio != null ? p(currentRatio > 2 ? `Current ratio of ${fmt(currentRatio,2)} indicates strong short-term liquidity — the company can comfortably cover its near-term obligations with liquid assets on hand.` : currentRatio > 1 ? `Current ratio of ${fmt(currentRatio,2)} shows the company has more current assets than liabilities, though the buffer is not particularly wide.` : `Current ratio below 1 (${fmt(currentRatio,2)}) means current liabilities exceed current assets — a potential liquidity concern worth monitoring.`) : ''}
        ` : ''}
      `);
